## Data & Workspace

OOUX data lives in two locations:

- **Published data**: `data/objects/*.json` â€” structured object definitions conforming to `data/schema.ts`
- **ORCA workspace**: `orca/{project-name}/` â€” iterative drafts from ORCA sessions

The workspace uses a draft-then-promote model:
1. ORCA skills write artifacts to `orca/{project}/` as markdown files
2. Each file tracks status in YAML frontmatter: `draft` â†’ `confirmed` â†’ `promoted`
3. The **orca-promote** skill syncs confirmed artifacts into `data/objects/*.json`

Existing object data can be read from `data/objects/` at any time. There are 26 object JSON files covering 13 core objects plus domain-specific objects.

## UI Design Rules

When designing or implementing UI from OOUX artifacts, apply the Caboodle UI rules: `ui-accessibility`, `ui-typography`, `ui-visual-design`, `ui-forms`, `ui-navigation`, `ui-interaction`, `ui-content`, and `ui-data-visualization`. The **orca-to-ui** skill translates object data into UI designs that follow these rules.

